<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="46" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,298]" pageId="2" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,151,177]" pageId="2" pageNumber="46">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Abdomen of male with basal pale yellow bands on tergites 
<number box="[1030,1076,152,178]" pageId="2" pageNumber="46" value="3.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="1.0">1–5</number>
, last two segments and genitalia dark brown; antennae pale brown; flagellum length 
<number box="[806,861,192,218]" pageId="2" pageNumber="46" value="0.74">0.74</number>
; fore coxa pale yellow, mid and hind coxae reddish brown; hind femur pale yellow with apical 
<number box="[751,802,232,258]" pageId="2" pageNumber="46" value="0.4">0.40</number>
reddish brown; wing length 
<number box="[1164,1204,232,258]" pageId="2" pageNumber="46" value="2.5">2.5</number>
; aedeagal complex membranous with distal portion pointed laterally and medially rounded, parameres with pointed tip.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
